# CLAUDE.md ‚Äî {{CONTRACTS_PKG}} (the contract layer)

> This package is the **single source of truth** for every request/response shape that crosses the
> backend‚Üîfrontend boundary. Treat it as protected core. Read this before touching anything here.

## The generation chain (one direction only)

```
hand-written Zod schemas   ‚îÄ‚îÄzod-to-openapi‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂   openapi.yaml   ‚îÄ‚îÄopenapi-typescript‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂   api-types
   (you write these)            (generated)        (generated)            (generated)
```

- **Zod is the source of truth.** Real runtime validation, Zod-first ‚Äî not OpenAPI-first.
- **`openapi.yaml` is generated.** Never hand-edit it. If it's wrong, fix the Zod schema and
  regenerate.
- **`api-types` (the generated TypeScript) is generated.** Never hand-edit it. The web app imports
  from `api-types`; the API validates incoming/outgoing payloads with the matching Zod schema at
  every route edge.

If you ever find yourself editing `openapi.yaml` or `api-types` by hand, stop ‚Äî you are editing an
output. Change the Zod schema instead.

## Layout

| Path | What it is | Who edits |
|------|-----------|-----------|
| `src/<module>.contract.ts` | one module's Zod schemas (request, response, params) | that module's agent |
| `src/index.ts` | append-only barrel: one `export *` line per module | each module appends ONE line |
| `openapi.yaml` | generated spec | nobody (generated) |
| `src/api-types.ts` (or `dist/`) | generated TS types | nobody (generated) |
| `package.json` `version` | the cross-track coordination signal | **integrator only** |

## The version bump is the ONLY cross-track coordination signal

- A bump of `{{CONTRACTS_PKG}}` `package.json` `version` tells the frontend "the contract changed ‚Äî
  resync your generated types." It is the single, explicit BE‚ÜîFE handshake.
- **ONLY the integrator bumps the version and regenerates** `openapi.yaml` + `api-types`, **once**,
  at merge. This is deliberate: if every parallel agent bumped the version and regenerated, every
  branch would collide on the same generated files and the version number would be meaningless.
- As a module agent: add your `*.contract.ts`, append your one `export *` line to `src/index.ts`,
  and STOP. Do not run the generator, do not bump the version. Flag the new/changed shape for the
  integrator in your ticket.

## Cross-field invariants go in `superRefine`

Single-field rules are plain Zod (`.min()`, `.email()`, enums). **Relationships between fields**
(end-after-start, "if A then B required", mutually-exclusive options, conditional requiredness) are
expressed with `.superRefine()` so the rule lives **in the contract**, validated identically on both
sides ‚Äî not re-implemented in a handler or a form.

```ts
export const {{EXAMPLE_SCHEMA}} = z.object({
  startsOn: z.string().date(),
  endsOn: z.string().date(),
  reason: z.string().optional(),
  kind: z.enum(["a", "b"]),
}).superRefine((v, ctx) => {
  if (v.endsOn < v.startsOn) {
    ctx.addIssue({ code: "custom", path: ["endsOn"], message: "must be on or after startsOn" });
  }
  if (v.kind === "b" && !v.reason) {
    ctx.addIssue({ code: "custom", path: ["reason"], message: "required when kind is b" });
  }
});
```

## Don't

- Don't hand-edit `openapi.yaml` or any generated `api-types`.
- Don't bump the version or regenerate in a feature branch ‚Äî integrator only.
- Don't re-implement a cross-field rule in a handler/form that you could express once in
  `superRefine`.
- Don't add a contract shape without the matching `export *` line in `src/index.ts`.
